headline: UPS (UPS) Q1 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: Carol Tome: Thank you, PJ, and good morning.  In the first quarter, our consolidated revenue was $21.5 billion, a decrease of 0.7% versus last year and in line with our expectations.  Consolidated operating profit was $1.8 billion, an increase of 0.9% compared to last year.

headline: UPS (UPS) Q4 2024 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: Joining me today are Carol Tomé, our CEO; Brian Dykes, our CFO and a few additional members of our executive leadership team.  Effective with the fourth quarter of 2024 USPS Air Cargo results have been moved from supply chain solutions to the U.S. domestic segment.  Not that U.S. domestic revenue per piece and cost per piece metrics are not impacted by this change as USPS transacts with us on a weight basis not on a per piece basis.

headline: UPS (UPS) Q2 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: For the second quarter of 2025, GAAP results include a net charge of $29 million or $0.04 per diluted share, comprised of after-tax transformation strategy costs of $57 million, which were partially offset by a $15 million gain from the divestiture of the business within Supply Chain Solutions and a $13 million benefit from the partial reversal of an income tax valuation allowance.  But due to our strategic actions, we saw a positive shift in the mix of business, as revenue declined by just 0.8%.

headline: New Owner of Longstanding Pak Mail in Lawrenceville, Georgia Brings Fresh Energy into the Business--Offering Shipping and Office Services
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., a leading franchisor in the packing, shipping, and office services industries, is pleased to announce the successful transfer of ownership of an existing Pak Mail location in Lawrenceville, GA to new owners, Pam and Tou Yee Moua. This transition to new ownership ensures that the community will benefit from the essential shipping and office services provided by this Pak Mail location for the last 31 years.
